that you're gonna wanna
take over as crew chief.

124
00:07:05,691 --> 00:07:07,093
(CHUCKLING)

125
00:07:08,194 --> 00:07:11,230
I don't know. I mean,

126
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:14,167
Bonnie's been after me
to cut back on
my boat hours, you know.

127
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,401
Jimmy, come on.

128
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:18,838
You've driven these boats.
You worked on these boats.

129
00:07:18,871 --> 00:07:21,073
You know this operation
better than anybody.

130
00:07:23,709 --> 00:07:24,944
Wow.

131
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:37,924
MIKE: Dad,
when you were drivin',
did you win a lot of races?

132
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:40,827
No, Son,
I never won any.

133
00:07:43,629 --> 00:07:47,099
Do some of the teams
bring people out
to the races with 'em?

134
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,236
Sure. The bigger teams
bring motor homes
full of people.

135
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:53,406
Kids, too?

136
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:55,641
(CHUCKLING)
I could do stuff for
the crew and everything.

137
00:07:55,675 --> 00:07:56,776
And I...
I know.

138
00:07:56,809 --> 00:07:58,778
I, I haven't even been
out of town before.

139
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:01,981
Only to Grandma's house,
and that's really
not that far.

140
00:08:02,014 --> 00:08:03,416
Mmm-hmm.

141
00:08:03,449 --> 00:08:07,053
Well, we'll have to
check with the boss
on this one, okay?

142
00:08:07,086 --> 00:08:08,621
All right.
All right.

143
00:08:10,189 --> 00:08:13,125
JIM: Just don't tell her
we had any of that
chicken, okay?

144
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,360
MIKE: Okay.

145
00:08:15,261 --> 00:08:16,696
BONNIE: There we go.

146
00:08:19,298 --> 00:08:21,100
So, Amy had a big day.

147
00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:23,603
Got home from work,
and I had the radio on.

148
00:08:23,636 --> 00:08:26,806
I was changin' her diaper,
and all of a sudden
out it came.

149
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:28,241
Out what came, honey?

150
00:08:28,274 --> 00:08:29,809
Her first word.

151
00:08:29,842 --> 00:08:31,244
At 11 months?
Mmm-hmm.

152
00:08:31,277 --> 00:08:33,079
Well, that's incredible.
BONNIE: I know.

153
00:08:33,112 --> 00:08:35,181
JIM: Little girl's
a regular certified genius.

154
00:08:35,214 --> 00:08:37,850
That's my girl.
Well, what did she say?

155
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,153
Agnew.
Agnew?

156
00:08:41,787 --> 00:08:42,855
As in Spiro.

157
00:08:42,889 --> 00:08:44,790
JIM: I know who
the man is, Bonnie.

158
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:46,626
Who's Spiro Agnew?

159
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:48,160
This is gonna get around,
you know.

160
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:49,695
Well, if you want,
I can tell 'em she said,

161
00:08:49,729 --> 00:08:51,664
"he's a low-down crook"
in the same breath.

162
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:58,170
Oh, come on, Jim.
Look at his hands.

163
00:09:04,977 --> 00:09:07,647
(MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

164
