(DOOR OPENING)

165
00:09:13,653 --> 00:09:15,488
Here you go.

166
00:09:16,656 --> 00:09:17,823
Is Mike asleep?

167
00:09:17,857 --> 00:09:19,859
Mmm-hmm. Finally.

168
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,395
Wanted to know what
his first word was.

169
00:09:22,428 --> 00:09:25,131
What was it, "Nixon"?

170
00:09:25,164 --> 00:09:27,433
Close. It was "Daddy."

171
00:09:30,703 --> 00:09:32,371
Listen, honey.

172
00:09:33,439 --> 00:09:36,075
There's somethin' I wanted
to talk to you about.

173
00:09:37,376 --> 00:09:40,646
Walker and Helen
are movin' to Indianapolis.

174
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:43,916
He asked me to
take over as team manager.

175
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:46,319
It was completely unexpected.
You said yes?

176
00:09:46,352 --> 00:09:48,321
I had to say yes.
How could you do that?

177
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:49,855
How can you say
it's unexpected, Jim?

178
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:51,657
Walker's been lookin'
for an excuse
to get out of here

179
00:09:51,691 --> 00:09:54,527
for the last five years
and you know it.

180
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,829
If we had any sense at all,
Jim, we'd go, too.
No, no, no.

181
00:09:56,862 --> 00:09:58,331
Let's not get started
on this.
Why, Jim?

182
00:09:58,364 --> 00:09:59,799
We're getting in
deeper and deeper, you know?

183
00:09:59,832 --> 00:10:02,368
How many people leave here
before you see
the writing on the wall?

184
00:10:02,401 --> 00:10:05,204
And what wall is this?
A wall from our house?

185
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:08,107
How many homes do we own
up in Indianapolis
or Cincinnati?

186
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:09,608
How many jobs
do we hold up there?

187
00:10:09,642 --> 00:10:12,912
How many jobs
did Owen have before
he went to Chicago, Jim?

188
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:14,814
Now, that's really
a fair comparison.

189
00:10:14,847 --> 00:10:16,849
Jim, he invited you
to partner with him.

190
00:10:21,487 --> 00:10:22,989
Good night, Bonnie.

191
00:10:26,659 --> 00:10:29,295
